Executive Summary
Randall Hogan joined Pentair in 1998 as EVP and President of the Enclosures Group (now known as Pentair Technical Solutions).  In 2001, he was appointed CEO and added responsibilities as Chairman a year later in 2002.  “We have been through a huge shift in the last few years, from 20 percent to 60 percent of our sales o 
Personal Attributes and Interests

Hogan and his wife, Sara, whom he met through classmate Joel Dewey, have two daughters, Emily and Kelly.
Hogan's decision to enter the water business was rooted in personal history. Before attending MIT, he spent two years  
Current Focus

Company Snapshot:  Pentair delivers industry-leading products, services and solutions for its customers' diverse needs in water and other fluids, thermal management and equipment protection. With 2015 revenues  
Key Challenges

